<!-- what is linc -->
 <div class="fdb-block block-background" data-block-type="contents" data-id="1" draggable="true">
  <div class="col-fill" style="background-image: url(/assets/home/lioness.jpg);">
  </div>
    <div class="row justify-content-end">
      <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
        <h1 class="text-center" style="color:white">What is LINC?</h1>
        <p class="lead lead-large lead-small text-center">LINC is an open source application comprised of an online database where researchers can upload and manage data on lions in their own study areas and identify unknown lions using LINC’s embedded artificial intelligence (AI) recognition technology. LINC also enables researchers to more easily share information with other lion researchers, promoting international and inter-organisational collaboration, thereby increasing the chances of detecting connections between lion populations.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="row row-large text-center mt-5 mb-5">
      <div class="col-12 col-sm-8 col-md-4 col-lg-3 m-sm-auto mr-md-auto ml-md-0">
        <img alt="image" class="img-fluid rounded" src="/assets/home/CommunityLogo.png">
        <h2><strong>COMMUNITY GENERATED DATABASE</strong></h2>
        <p>Researchers across the continent can capture, organize and share lion observation data with one another.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-12 col-sm-8 col-md-4 col-lg-3 m-sm-auto pt-5 pt-md-0">
        <img alt="image" class="img-fluid rounded" src="/assets/home/CompIcon.png">
        <h2><strong>EASY TO USE WEBSITE</strong></h2>
        <p>With its user-friendly interface that maximizes efficiency in work flow, LINC is leading the paradigm shift away from paper records and distributed data.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-12 col-sm-8 col-md-4 col-lg-3 m-sm-auto ml-md-auto mr-md-0 pt-5 pt-md-0">
        <img alt="image" class="img-fluid rounded" src="/assets/home/Tick_1.png">
          <h2><strong>LION RECOGNITION SOFTWARE</strong></h2>
          <p>An automated facial and whisker recognition software allows users to easily compare photographs of unknown lions to an expansive database of individuals, helping to identify lions who move beyond organizations’ study areas.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>



